text: Tallashua Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Tallashua is a name derived from the Choctaw language meaning "palmettos are there". Variant names are "Talasha Creek", "Tallasher Creek", and "Tallashuah Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Neshoba County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Newton County, Mississippi
title: Tallashua Creek
